description_narrative:
This project seeks to improve the effectiveness of UNESCO's support to Caribbean SIDS in the implementation of the 2003 Convention, notably by building capacities on the preparation of nomination files for the Lists of the 2003 Convention. To this end, the project will:

a) Ensure update of the UNESCO capacity-building materials on nominations aligned with the conclusions of the global reflection on the listing mechanisms of the 2003 Convention;
b) Delivery an online training course with selected participants on preparing nominations to the Lists of the 2003 Convention;
c) Facilitate South-South cooperation, peer learning and networking among trained participants.
